DIV1.P:
3. And lastly; FROM God they receive the Rewards of their Fidelity to His Service.
For He will not keep back the Hire of His Labourers, that have reaped down His Corn;
but He will certainly distribute to every Man his Peny, when they shall rest from their Labours; their Work (the Rewards of it) shall follow them. He will overlook the Frailties and Infirmities of his faithful Ministers, blot out their Trans∣gressions, and say to them, Well done good and faithful Servants, enter into the Joy of your Lord. And tho' they may not ascend with equal Triumph, yet they shall with equal Safe∣ty with Elijah, into the Heavens prepared for them.
